Hmm?

14:03.877 --> 14:05.076
I'm up next.

14:05.078 --> 14:08.847
On a scale of 9 to 10,
how do I look?

14:08.849 --> 14:10.315
You look beautiful,

14:10.317 --> 14:11.883
so they're gonna
be really surprised

14:11.885 --> 14:13.484
when you have jokes.

14:13.486 --> 14:16.955
And our next storyteller
is here for the first time,

14:16.957 --> 14:20.692
reading a tale so epic
that it should be two tales.

14:20.694 --> 14:23.628
And like the two-tailed
Melusina,

14:23.630 --> 14:26.831
a serpent of European
folklore...

14:28.000 --> 14:29.868
She is truly a beauty.

14:29.870 --> 14:34.873
What in good God
is that man talking about?

14:34.875 --> 14:39.244
Please welcome
Caroline Channing.

14:39.246 --> 14:42.580
[applause, snaps]

14:42.582 --> 14:46.284
As he said, my name
is Caroline Channing.

14:46.286 --> 14:48.853
That used to mean
something special,

14:48.855 --> 14:52.156
and I have learned
through the past few years

14:52.158 --> 14:54.525
that it still does.

14:54.527 --> 14:56.527
My father was Martin Channing,

14:56.529 --> 14:58.429
the most hated man
in New York City.

14:58.431 --> 15:01.900
Except for any
Time Warner Cable guy...

15:04.169 --> 15:05.370
You know what?

15:05.372 --> 15:06.971
I don't need to look at this.

15:06.973 --> 15:08.172
I know what happened.

15:08.174 --> 15:09.607
I'll never forget it.

15:09.609 --> 15:12.443
You don't forget the day
that you lose yourself.

15:12.445 --> 15:14.979
[groaning]
Oh, boy.

15:14.981 --> 15:16.981
She's off script.

15:16.983 --> 15:19.183
She's gone rogue.

15:19.185 --> 15:20.919
Where's that waitress?

15:20.921 --> 15:22.854
Double his double!

15:22.856 --> 15:24.689
♪

15:28.394 --> 15:30.495
As my driver drove
down 5th Avenue

15:30.497 --> 15:32.430
and up to my townhouse,

15:32.432 --> 15:35.433
I saw there was
a police car parked out front.

15:35.435 --> 15:39.304
And at first, I thought,
"Am I being arrested?"

15:39.306 --> 15:42.540
Lip-synching to Ludacris
at a stoplight!

15:44.209 --> 15:46.444
But it was my father
being arrested.

15:46.446 --> 15:50.348
I saw my father in handcuffs.

15:50.350 --> 15:54.252
There, in that instant,

15:54.254 --> 15:57.255
I went from princess
to pariah.

15:57.257 --> 15:58.456
[scoffs]

15:58.458 --> 16:00.291
Well, she threw away
a perfectly good

16:00.293 --> 16:02.260
"Pariah Carey" joke.

16:02.262 --> 16:03.895
Shh!

16:04.964 --> 16:07.031
Just looking out
for my girl here.

16:07.033 --> 16:08.700
(both)
Shh!

16:09.868 --> 16:13.638
My perfect world
was shattered.

16:13.640 --> 16:17.041
I saw the man who I trusted,

16:17.043 --> 16:20.178
who I believed in
more than anyone,

16:20.180 --> 16:23.581
who read me bedtime stories

16:23.583 --> 16:26.751
and taught me how to tie
my shoes with bunny ears...

16:26.753 --> 16:29.554
I saw my father in handcuffs.

16:29.556 --> 16:32.056
He stole my trust,

16:32.058 --> 16:33.925
my belief in people,

16:33.927 --> 16:35.159
my innocence.

16:35.161 --> 16:39.297
If she doesn't say "virginity,"
I am leaving.

16:39.299 --> 16:42.266
He stole who I thought I was

16:42.268 --> 16:47.238
and left me to find
who I really am.

16:47.240 --> 16:49.507
Thank you.

16:52.011 --> 16:53.011
Nothing?

16:53.013 --> 16:54.112
[scoffs]

16:54.114 --> 16:55.847
We got to sneak her
out the back door.

16:55.849 --> 16:58.850
[applause]

17:06.825 --> 17:10.928
You were so sad
and triumphant

17:10.930 --> 17:12.130
and...so...

17:12.132 --> 17:13.331
[sobs]

17:13.333 --> 17:15.199
Oh, here come the waterworks!

17:15.201 --> 17:16.501
[sobbing]

17:16.503 --> 17:18.436
Caroline,

17:18.438 --> 17:21.205
I know you said
you never would,

17:21.207 --> 17:23.875
but you touched me.

17:25.077 --> 17:28.513
That really tugged
at my heartstrings...

17:28.515 --> 17:29.914
or cables or wires

17:29.916 --> 17:32.750
or whatever's in here
keeping me alive.

17:32.752 --> 17:35.753
[moaning]
Caroline...

17:35.755 --> 17:39.791
Oh, you know what
you and I both need?

17:39.793 --> 17:42.393
A hug. Yeah.

17:42.395 --> 17:44.095
Oh...

17:47.166 --> 17:50.001
It's nice, isn't it?

17:51.370 --> 17:52.970
Caroline,
that was great!

17:52.972 --> 17:57.275
I'm so glad I inspired you
with my awesome story.

17:57.277 --> 17:58.476
You're still here?

17:58.478 --> 18:00.845
[scoffs]

18:00.847 --> 18:03.414
I'm sorry I didn't
do your jokes, Max.

18:03.416 --> 18:04.415
You know what?

18:04.417 --> 18:05.716
You didn't need them!

18:05.718 --> 18:08.119
I think people sometimes
like to be sad.

18:08.121 --> 18:10.054
That's why there's Adele.

18:11.390 --> 18:13.624
I think I finally
got closure.

18:13.626 --> 18:15.126
It's gone, Max.

18:15.128 --> 18:17.195
Love you.

18:17.197 --> 18:18.396
Love your story.

18:18.398 --> 18:19.597
Thanks.

18:19.599 --> 18:20.865
I'm Nina Spiegel.

18:20.867 --> 18:22.733
I found the whole thing
riveting.

18:22.735 --> 18:25.269
The ups, the downs,
the way-downs.

18:25.271 --> 18:27.472
Ugh, your story had it all.

18:27.474 --> 18:29.807
She's not joining
your threesome.

18:31.009 --> 18:32.643
Sorry, that's usually
what women want

18:32.645 --> 18:34.312
when they compliment me.

18:34.314 --> 18:37.448
Look, I'd like to talk about
taking this to my studio.

18:37.450 --> 18:40.785
You have your own
studio apartment?

18:40.787 --> 18:43.221
Let the wooing continue.

18:43.223 --> 18:45.056
No, it's a film studio.

18:45.058 --> 18:46.457
Warner Brothers.

18:46.459 --> 18:49.660
The Tasmanian Devil
Warner Brothers?

18:51.130 --> 18:54.332
I think we can turn your story
into a movie.

18:54.334 --> 18:55.867
Really?

18:55.869 --> 18:57.568
The Caroline Channing story

18:57.570 --> 18:59.337
deserves to live
on the big screen

18:59.339 --> 19:01.472
for one to two weeks.

19:01.474 --> 19:04.108
Then On Demand
for eternity.

19:04.110 --> 19:06.711
Oh, my God.

19:06.713 --> 19:09.113
Max, isn't this exciting?

19:09.115 --> 19:10.381
I know!

19:10.383 --> 19:13.317
They have Speedy Gonzalez too!

19:13.319 --> 19:17.588
♪

19:17.590 --> 19:19.223
I'm still on hold, Max.

19:19.225 --> 19:20.691
I know Nina's important,

19:20.693 --> 19:22.727
because her assistant
has put me on hold six times

19:22.729 --> 19:24.495
and muted me twice.

19:24.497 --> 19:27.098
Muting you's an option?

19:27.100 --> 19:29.867
Why wouldn't they
put that in your manual?

19:29.869 --> 19:30.868
Hi!

19:30.870 --> 19:32.270
Oh, are you kidding?

19:32.272 --> 19:33.905
I love waiting.

19:35.040 --> 19:38.075
Sophie, here's
your consolation gnocchi,

19:38.077 --> 19:41.312
for not finding somebody
to get gn-knocked up.

19:41.314 --> 19:44.215
Oh, thanks, Oleg.

19:44.217 --> 19:48.753
Well, at least I have you.

19:49.555 --> 19:51.222
You know what, Sophie?

19:51.224 --> 19:52.690
I'll be the surrogate,

19:52.692 --> 19:54.759
but if my pregnancy boobs
knock over a street lamp,

19:54.761 --> 19:56.294
that's on your insurance.

19:56.296 --> 19:58.396
That's real nice of you, Max,

19:58.398 --> 20:02.200
but if there's anything that
I learned from Caroline's story,

20:02.202 --> 20:07.004
it's that you can't give up,
even if you should.

20:07.006 --> 20:08.573
Oh, so you're gonna
keep trying?

20:08.575 --> 20:10.341
No, we're gonna adopt,

20:10.343 --> 20:13.010
and we will cherish
this little baby,

20:13.012 --> 20:15.379
even if it's not
technically from us.

20:15.381 --> 20:16.714
Yeah, Oleg's right.

20:16.716 --> 20:19.951
I mean, half my hair's
not from me,

20:19.953 --> 20:24.655
but I love it just as much
as if it were.

20:24.657 --> 20:28.726
They are flying me
to Hollywood!

20:28.728 --> 20:30.228
They wan to bring me out
first class

20:30.230 --> 20:31.429
for a meet-and-greet.

20:31.431 --> 20:32.630
But I told them no.

20:32.632 --> 20:34.465
Are you crazy?

20:34.467 --> 20:36.000
You can't pass up
a meet-and-greet.

20:36.002 --> 20:37.668
You can't pass up
any kind of meat.

20:37.670 --> 20:39.136
You're anemic.

20:39.138 --> 20:41.572
I switched the tickets
for two coach seats.

20:41.574 --> 20:42.773
I want you to come with me!

20:42.775 --> 20:44.175
Who needs to lie flat

20:44.177 --> 20:45.977
when I can be squished
between my best friend

20:45.979 --> 20:49.213
and an obese rabbi in row 36?

20:49.215 --> 20:51.082
We're going to Hollywood!

20:51.084 --> 20:56.087
♪
